article.description: McClelland, Williams help San Diego beat Dayton
article.headline: McClelland, Williams help San Diego beat Dayton
article.linkText: McClelland, Williams help San Diego beat Dayton
article.story: SAN DIEGO -- Keith Williams threw for two touchdowns and ran for another, Dallas Kessman ran for 102 yards and two scores, and Troy McClelland had a late interception to help San Diego beat Dayton 40-29 in a key Pioneer League game Saturday night. San Diego (6-1, 4-1) scored 20 fourth-quarter points on touchdown runs by Kessman, Chris Campano and Williams. Kessman tied the game on a 7-yard run early the fourth quarter, but a bobbled hold on the ensuing PAT left it tied at 26-26. Dayton (5-2, 3-1) then capped a 10-play, 67-yard drive with a 24-yard field goal by William Will about five minutes later. After exchanging punts, Campano scored from a yard out and San Diego led 33-29 with 2:31 left. On the ensuing Dayton drive, McClelland picked off a Will Bardo pass and returned it 27-yards, to the Dayton 14 and Williams added a 13-yard touchdown run.
